body:
Thanks for the PR. I think the fix is a little more involved. I haven't checked all the cases, but one example in `ReplicaManager`:

```scala
def startup() {
    // start ISR expiration thread
    // A follower can lag behind leader for up to config.replicaLagTimeMaxMs x 1.5 before it is removed from ISR
    scheduler.schedule("isr-expiration", maybeShrinkIsr _, period = config.replicaLagTimeMaxMs / 2, unit = TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)
    scheduler.schedule("isr-change-propagation", maybePropagateIsrChanges _, period = 2500L, unit = TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)
  }
```

We would want to stop these tasks in `ReplicaManager.shutdown` (which we don't seem to do) if we want to avoid an exception from being thrown after the scheduler is shutdown. We should look for other cases where there are tasks that are executed periodically.
